<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2017-12-31</DATELINE><TITLE>One Health Central and Eastern Africa: Historical and Future Perspectives</TITLE><BODY>Abstract One Health Central and Eastern Africa (OHCEA) is a network of schools of public health and veterinary higher education institutions that are located in countries of the Eastern and Central Africa region, a region that includes the Congo Basin commonly considered to be one of the ‘hot spots’ for emerging and reemerging infectious diseases. The vision of the OHCEA network is to be a global leader in One Health, promoting sustainable health for prosperous communities, productive animals, and balanced ecosystems.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>